  16 class _LockFileEncoder(json.JSONEncoder):
  17     """A specilized JSON encoder to convert loaded data into a lock file.
  18 
  19     This adds a few characteristics to the encoder:
  20 
  21     * The JSON is always prettified with indents and spaces.
  22     * The output is always UTF-8-encoded text, never binary, even on Python 2.
  23     """
  24     def __init__(self):
  25         super(_LockFileEncoder, self).__init__(
  26             indent=4, separators=(",", ": "), sort_keys=True,
  27         )
  28 
  29     def encode(self, obj):
  30         content = super(_LockFileEncoder, self).encode(obj)
  31         if not isinstance(content, six.text_type):
  32             content = content.decode("utf-8")
  33         content += "\n"
  34         return content
  35 
  36     def iterencode(self, obj):
  37         for chunk in super(_LockFileEncoder, self).iterencode(obj):
  38             if not isinstance(chunk, six.text_type):
  39                 chunk = chunk.decode("utf-8")
  40             yield chunk
  41         yield "\n"
  42 
  43 
  44 LOCKFILE_SECTIONS = {
  45     "_meta": Meta,
  46     "default": PackageCollection,
  47     "develop": PackageCollection,
  48 }
  49 
  50 PIPFILE_SPEC_CURRENT = 6
  51 
  52 
  53 def _copy_jsonsafe(value):
  54     """Deep-copy a value into JSON-safe types.
  55     """
  56     if isinstance(value, six.string_types + (numbers.Number,)):
  57         return value
  58     if isinstance(value, collections_abc.Mapping):
  59         return {six.text_type(k): _copy_jsonsafe(v) for k, v in value.items()}
  60     if isinstance(value, collections_abc.Iterable):
  61         return [_copy_jsonsafe(v) for v in value]
  62     if value is None:   # This doesn't happen often for us.
  63         return None
  64     return six.text_type(value)

  67 class Lockfile(DataView):
  68     """Representation of a Pipfile.lock.
  69     """
  70     __SCHEMA__ = {
  71         "_meta": {"type": "dict", "required": True},
  72         "default": {"type": "dict", "required": True},
  73         "develop": {"type": "dict", "required": True},
  74     }
  75 
  76     @classmethod
  77     def validate(cls, data):
  78         super(Lockfile, cls).validate(data)
  79         for key, klass in LOCKFILE_SECTIONS.items():
  80             klass.validate(data[key])
  81 
  82     @classmethod
  83     def load(cls, f, encoding=None):
  84         if encoding is None:
  85             data = json.load(f)
  86         else:
  87             data = json.loads(f.read().decode(encoding))
  88         return cls(data)
  89 
  90     @classmethod
  91     def with_meta_from(cls, pipfile):
  92         data = {
  93             "_meta": {
  94                 "hash": _copy_jsonsafe(pipfile.get_hash()._data),
  95                 "pipfile-spec": PIPFILE_SPEC_CURRENT,
  96                 "requires": _copy_jsonsafe(pipfile._data.get("requires", {})),
  97                 "sources": _copy_jsonsafe(pipfile.sources._data),
  98             },
  99             "default": {},
 100             "develop": {},
 101         }
 102         return cls(data)
 103 
 104     def __getitem__(self, key):
 105         value = self._data[key]
 106         try:
 107             return LOCKFILE_SECTIONS[key](value)
 108         except KeyError:
 109             return value
 110 
 111     def __setitem__(self, key, value):
 112         if isinstance(value, DataView):
 113             self._data[key] = value._data
 114         else:
 115             self._data[key] = value
 116 
 117     def is_up_to_date(self, pipfile):
 118         return self.meta.hash == pipfile.get_hash()
 119 
 120     def dump(self, f, encoding=None):
 121         encoder = _LockFileEncoder()
 122         if encoding is None:
 123             for chunk in encoder.iterencode(self._data):
 124                 f.write(chunk)
 125         else:
 126             content = encoder.encode(self._data)
 127             f.write(content.encode(encoding))
 128

 130     def meta(self):
 131         try:
 132             return self["_meta"]
 133         except KeyError:
 134             raise AttributeError("meta")
 135

 137     def meta(self, value):
 138         self["_meta"] = value

 145             raise AttributeError("meta")
